 (230, 2, '2016-06-29 12:43:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 'Auto Draft', '', 'auto-draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2016-06-29 12:43:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'https://insightba.net/?page_id=230', 4, 'page', '', 0),
 (231, 2, '2016-06-29 12:44:29', '2016-06-29 16:44:29', '<b>Fully insured </b><b>health carriers </b><b>charge </b><b><i>set monthly premiums </i></b><b>regardless of </b><b>the actual </b><b>claim </b><b>costs incurred by covered members. Self-funding </b><b>allows an employer to pay </b><b><i>for only the claims incurred </i></b><b>by its covered members. </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Self-funded coverage </b><b>consists of monthly claims </b><b>costs, reinsurance </b><b>(stop loss) premium </b><b>and third party </b><b>administration (TPA) </b><b>costs. Fully insured coverage consists of </b><b>set  premiums from the insurance </b><b>carrier.</b><b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>O</b><b>utside of continually increasing members’ out-of-pocket exposure (deductibles, copays and coinsurance) the employer has limited ability to impact annual premium increases.   </b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Unlike fully insured health carriers that charge a set amount of premiums regardless of the claim costs, self-funding allows an employer to pay for only the claims incurred by its covered members.  <span style="color: #ff6600;">(insert graphic)</span></b>\r\n\r\nThe Role of the TPA (Third Party Administrator)\r\n\r\n<b>A </b><b>Third Party Administrator (TPA</b><b>), like Insight Benefit Administrators, provides </b><b>overall administration of the plan. </b> <b>TPA </b><b>services are tailored to your needs and include:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - </b><b>reviewing and paying claims </b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - customer </b><b>service for covered members and the employer</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  </b><b>- assistance with selecting appropriate </b><b>stop </b><b>loss </b>\r\n\r\n<b>  </b><b>- access to local and national provider networks</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - pharmacy benefit management </b><b>(PBM) services</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Stop Loss or Reinsurance</b><b>: </b><b>Your Safety </b><b>Net</b>\r\n\r\n<b>There are two basic types of </b><b>stop loss coverage</b><b>:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>SPECIFIC COVERAGE: </b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - Specific coverage is purchased to protect the employer from individual high claimants. </b><b>When an individual members’ claims reach a certain </b><b>dollar </b><b>amount, any claims above </b><b>that </b><b>are </b><b>then covered by the reinsurance carrier.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>AGGREGATE COVERAGE:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - Aggregate coverage is purchased to protect the employer from high claimants across the employer group. Any claims dollars incurred above a certain dollar amount (also known as the Attachment Point) are then covered by the reinsurance carrier. </b>', 'Self funded versus fully-funded', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-is-self-funding-different-from-fully-funded', '', '', '2016-07-07 09:25:09', '2016-07-07 13:25:09', '', 147, 'https://insightba.net/?page_id=231', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (233, 2, '2016-06-29 12:44:29', '2016-06-29 16:44:29', '<b>Fully insured </b><b>health carriers </b><b>charge </b><b><i>set monthly premiums </i></b><b>regardless of </b><b>the actual </b><b>claim </b><b>costs incurred by covered members. Self-funding </b><b>allows an employer to pay </b><b><i>for only the claims incurred </i></b><b>by its covered members. </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Self-funded coverage </b><b>consists of monthly claims </b><b>costs, reinsurance </b><b>(stop loss) premium </b><b>and third party </b><b>administration (TPA) </b><b>costs. Fully insured coverage consists of </b><b>set insurance </b><b>carrier </b><b>premiums. </b>\r\n\r\n<b>And </b><b>outside of continually increasing members’ out-of-pocket exposure (deductibles, copays and coinsurance) the employer has limited ability to impact annual premium increases.   </b>', 'How is self-funding different from fully-funded?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '231-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-29 12:44:29', '2016-06-29 16:44:29', '', 231, 'https://insightba.net/231-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
 (234, 2, '2016-06-30 09:41:32', '2016-06-30 13:41:32', '<b>Fully insured </b><b>health carriers </b><b>charge </b><b><i>set monthly premiums </i></b><b>regardless of </b><b>the actual </b><b>claim </b><b>costs incurred by covered members. Self-funding </b><b>allows an employer to pay </b><b><i>for only the claims incurred </i></b><b>by its covered members. </b>\n\n<b>Self-funded coverage </b><b>consists of monthly claims </b><b>costs, reinsurance </b><b>(stop loss) premium </b><b>and third party </b><b>administration (TPA) </b><b>costs. Fully insured coverage consists of </b><b>set  premiums from the insurance </b><b>carrier.</b><b> </b>\n\n<b>O</b><b>utside of continually increasing members’ out-of-pocket exposure (deductibles, copays and coinsurance) the employer has limited ability to impact annual premium increases.   </b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Unlike fully insured health carriers that charge a set amount of premiums regardless of the claim costs, self-funding allows an employer to pay for only the claims incurred by its covered members.  <span style="color: #ff6600;">(insert graphic)</span></b>\n\nThe Role of the TPA (Third Party Administrator)\n\n<b>A </b><b>Third Party Administrator (TPA</b><b>), like Insight Benefit Administrators, provides </b><b>overall administration of the plan. </b> <b>TPA </b><b>services are tailored to your needs and include:</b>\n\n<b>  - </b><b>reviewing and paying claims </b>\n\n<b>  - customer </b><b>service for covered members and the employer</b>\n\n<b>  </b><b>- assistance with selecting appropriate </b><b>stop </b><b>loss </b>\n\n<b>  </b><b>- access to local and national provider networks</b>\n\n<b>  - pharmacy benefit management </b><b>(PBM) services</b>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Stop Loss or Reinsurance</b><b>: </b><b>Your Safety </b><b>Net</b>\n\n<b>There are two basic types of </b><b>stop loss coverage</b><b>:</b>\n\n<b>SPECIFIC COVERAGE: </b>\n\n<b>  - Specific coverage is purchased to protect the employer from individual high claimants. </b><b>When an individual members’ claims reach a certain </b><b>dollar </b><b>amount, any claims above </b><b>that </b><b>are </b><b>then covered by the reinsurance carrier.</b>\n\n<b>AGGREGATE COVERAGE:</b>\n\n<b>  - Aggregate coverage is purchased to protect the employer from high claimants across the employer group. Any claims dollars incurred above a certain dollar amount (also known as the Attachment Point) are then covered by the reinsurance carrier. </b>', 'How is self-funding different from fully-funded?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '231-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-06-30 09:41:32', '2016-06-30 13:41:32', '', 231, 'https://insightba.net/231-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
 (235, 2, '2016-06-29 12:47:56', '2016-06-29 16:47:56', '<b>Fully insured </b><b>health carriers </b><b>charge </b><b><i>set monthly premiums </i></b><b>regardless of </b><b>the actual </b><b>claim </b><b>costs incurred by covered members. Self-funding </b><b>allows an employer to pay </b><b><i>for only the claims incurred </i></b><b>by its covered members. </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Self-funded coverage </b><b>consists of monthly claims </b><b>costs, reinsurance </b><b>(stop loss) premium </b><b>and third party </b><b>administration (TPA) </b><b>costs. Fully insured coverage consists of </b><b>set insurance </b><b>carrier </b><b>premiums. </b>\r\n\r\n<b>And </b><b>outside of continually increasing members’ out-of-pocket exposure (deductibles, copays and coinsurance) the employer has limited ability to impact annual premium increases.   </b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Unlike fully insured health carriers that charge a set amount of premiums regardless of the claim costs, self-funding allows an employer to pay for only the claims incurred by its covered members.  <span style="color: #ff6600;">(insert graphic)</span></b>\r\n\r\nThe Role of the TPA (Third Party Administrator)\r\n\r\n<b>A </b><b>Third Party Administrator (TPA</b><b>), like Insight Benefit Administrators, provides </b><b>overall administration of the plan. </b> <b>TPA </b><b>services are tailored to your needs and include:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - </b><b>reviewing and paying claims </b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - customer </b><b>service for covered members and the employer</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  </b><b>- assistance with selecting appropriate </b><b>stop </b><b>loss </b>\r\n\r\n<b>  </b><b>- access to local and national provider networks</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - pharmacy benefit management </b><b>(PBM) services</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Stop Loss or Reinsurance</b><b>: </b><b>Your Safety </b><b>Net</b>\r\n\r\n<b>There are two basic types of </b><b>stop loss coverage</b><b>:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>SPECIFIC COVERAGE: </b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - Specific coverage is purchased to protect the employer from individual high claimants. </b><b>When an individual members’ claims reach a certain </b><b>dollar </b><b>amount, any claims above </b><b>that </b><b>are </b><b>then covered by the reinsurance carrier.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>AGGREGATE COVERAGE:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - Aggregate coverage is purchased to protect the employer from high claimants across the employer group. Any claims dollars incurred above a certain dollar amount (also known as the Attachment Point) are then covered by the reinsurance carrier. </b>', 'How is self-funding different from fully-funded?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '231-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-29 12:47:56', '2016-06-29 16:47:56', '', 231, 'https://insightba.net/231-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
 (255, 2, '2016-07-07 09:25:09', '2016-07-07 13:25:09', '<b>Fully insured </b><b>health carriers </b><b>charge </b><b><i>set monthly premiums </i></b><b>regardless of </b><b>the actual </b><b>claim </b><b>costs incurred by covered members. Self-funding </b><b>allows an employer to pay </b><b><i>for only the claims incurred </i></b><b>by its covered members. </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Self-funded coverage </b><b>consists of monthly claims </b><b>costs, reinsurance </b><b>(stop loss) premium </b><b>and third party </b><b>administration (TPA) </b><b>costs. Fully insured coverage consists of </b><b>set  premiums from the insurance </b><b>carrier.</b><b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>O</b><b>utside of continually increasing members’ out-of-pocket exposure (deductibles, copays and coinsurance) the employer has limited ability to impact annual premium increases.   </b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Unlike fully insured health carriers that charge a set amount of premiums regardless of the claim costs, self-funding allows an employer to pay for only the claims incurred by its covered members.  <span style="color: #ff6600;">(insert graphic)</span></b>\r\n\r\nThe Role of the TPA (Third Party Administrator)\r\n\r\n<b>A </b><b>Third Party Administrator (TPA</b><b>), like Insight Benefit Administrators, provides </b><b>overall administration of the plan. </b> <b>TPA </b><b>services are tailored to your needs and include:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - </b><b>reviewing and paying claims </b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - customer </b><b>service for covered members and the employer</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  </b><b>- assistance with selecting appropriate </b><b>stop </b><b>loss </b>\r\n\r\n<b>  </b><b>- access to local and national provider networks</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - pharmacy benefit management </b><b>(PBM) services</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Stop Loss or Reinsurance</b><b>: </b><b>Your Safety </b><b>Net</b>\r\n\r\n<b>There are two basic types of </b><b>stop loss coverage</b><b>:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>SPECIFIC COVERAGE: </b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - Specific coverage is purchased to protect the employer from individual high claimants. </b><b>When an individual members’ claims reach a certain </b><b>dollar </b><b>amount, any claims above </b><b>that </b><b>are </b><b>then covered by the reinsurance carrier.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>AGGREGATE COVERAGE:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>  - Aggregate coverage is purchased to protect the employer from high claimants across the employer group. Any claims dollars incurred above a certain dollar amount (also known as the Attachment Point) are then covered by the reinsurance carrier. </b>', 'Self funded versus fully-funded', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '231-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-07 09:25:09', '2016-07-07 13:25:09', '', 231, 'https://insightba.net/231-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
